sec.p:
A FLF must be diluted with water before it is applied. Undiluted FLF increase the risk of low nutrient absorption, injury to the leaf surface, or general phytotoxicity [8]. Ideal concentrations of foliar-applied nutrient solutions depend on the plant species, plant age, nutritional status and weather conditions [29]. In the case of FLF, common concentrations range between 3% and 7%. If minerals are added, a dilution to reach a concentration of 2% is adequate. Used in short intervals, the dilution should be higher. Ash (150 g L
- 1
) and raw soap (2 g L
- 1
) can be added to the diluted FLF to enhance its adhesiveness on the crops. Cactus juice, aloe, and molasses have a similar adhesive effect [11].

